  "text": "For orthogonal range searching (or axis-aligned rectangles), the picture is more muddy. On the lower bound side, Beck [CITATION_1] proved that there exists a set P of n points in R 2 , such that disc(P, B 2 ) = Ω(lg n), where we use B d to denote the family containing all axis-aligned rectangles in R d . However, in dimensions d ≥ 3, the highest achieved lower bound is only Ω(lg",
