    "37531613": {
      "title": "Balanced two-colorings of finite sets in the square I",
      "abstract": "LetT(N) be the least integer such that one can assign ± 1’s to anyN points in the unit square so that the sum of these values in any rectangle with sides parallel to those of the square have absolute value at mostT(N). G. Tusnadi asked what could be said about the order of magnitude ofT(N). We prove ::: ::: $$\\log N \\ll T(N) \\ll (\\log N)^4 .$$"
